She turned to an empty page and noted the date. Below, she wrote "11.5.648–13.12.648".
"Are you refreshing old memories?" Ivory asked and looked at the old notebook. Kari nodded. "Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? After all, it's only a few days away."
Kari knocked twice on the lantern. "No," as Ivory had suspected. The Ice King never let Kari out, as he regarded her as a "blemish." She was born deaf and was the only daughter in the family; her siblings were all boys.
Similar things applied to Ivory as well. When Ivory came out as non-binary, it seemed like the world was changing. As punishment for this difference, Ivory received tasks where she spent most of the time alone.
Additionally, Ivory was also forced to serve the princess. But it didn't matter much to Ivory, as she gained a friend in the process.
"You're having a birthday soon, right?" Ivory asked, remembering that the princess had a birthday in a few days. Kari nodded, her bright blue eyes flickering with sadness.
"Do you want to celebrate your birthday?" Ivory asked, thinking about the last time the princess had answered this question.
"No," Kari replied. Ivory knew this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother was banished. At the time, Ivory was just a baby, but she remembered how upset the servants and the city's residents were. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen and that she could even predict things that would later come true.
"What do you want to do now?" Ivory asked. Kari looked at Ivory excitedly. She held a piece of paper in her hand.
